{
  "stem": "14900.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "There wasn't that much space to lay on the ground, but we combined them so that we had a couple-- three blankets under us, three over us.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we used to sleep like sardines, curled into each other for body warmth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was gettin' very cold.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I don't know which one of them decided.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I was the baby.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "I was 14.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The oldest were a woman by the name of Sala and Hinda.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They were both 38.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "They were the communist leaders.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Then there was a girl I became very close to, that I adored.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Her name was Basha.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "She was 18.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "Those three were the leaders, especially Hinda and Basha, more so than Sala.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "We marched right under the lookouts' noses, singing songs in Polish that were quite revolutionary-- made us feel good-- to take a daily shower.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "Now, mind you, it was just a pipe attached to a fence with a sieve [LAUGHS] on the end.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "It was freezing, ice-cold out there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "The ground was hard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "If it thawed, we had muck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "We'd strip off our clothes-- our dress.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "I mean, there was no other clothing-- and stand under that water and wash ourselves to prevent disease.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "Because by then, the lice had come with everybody from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "Well, that's the way life went on in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "Until one day, we went through a selection for a transport again, this time into Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "Now, the difference between Bergen-Belsen and Auschwitz was that Bergen-Belsen was supposed to be the selection place for labor camps.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "There were no ovens, no gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "And one more time, we were-- all of us, our whole group, was selected for a labor transport into Germany-- cattle trains, true.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
